<h2 class="bac">Summary:</h2>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Strong A&ndash;level Grades and on track for a minimum 2:1 degree (or equivalent)</li>
	<li>Primary locations: Opportunities in London</li>
	<li>Desk&ndash;specific, 9&ndash;week programme from June – August</li>
	<li>Treasury – Funding (Money Market Trading and Analyst roles)</li>
	<li>Treasury – Liquidity Risk (Analyst and Reporting roles)</li>
	<li>Online application form</li>
	<li>Application Deadline: 17 December 2010</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Within Bank of America Merrill Lynch, International Corporate Treasury is a central function whose activities have enterprise&ndash;wide impact. The goal of International Corporate Treasury is to optimise shareholder value by providing world&ndash;class management of capital, liquidity, interest rate and operational risk. It is also responsible for creating a state&ndash;of&ndash;the&ndash;art framework for managing the tradeoffs between risk and return, and for training and exporting enterprise leaders.  
</p>
<p class="bac">
A career in Treasury allows you to be forward&ndash;thinking and instrumental to our future strategy. Your day will be varied and challenging, and will allow you to extend your skills in various disciplines, adding value to your role.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
The Summer Intern Programme within International Corporate Treasury is a precursor to the Full Time Programme. As a Summer Analyst, you&#39;ll work for nine weeks in International Corporate Treasury in roles that mirror the positions of full&ndash;time analysts. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
These could include the following:  
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Partnering the International Treasury Traders who operate within the short&ndash;term money markets, in order to execute the daily funding strategy and to optimise the management of the company&#39;s balance sheet</li>
	<li>Supporting the liquidity risk management team in meeting regulatory requirements at the heart of the response to the global financial crisis. Varied tasks include liquidity risk measurement, allocation and pricing stress testing, cash flow modelling, defining liquidity/collateral pool, assessing funding plans and new product reviews.</li>
	<li>Analysing data and output from the company&#39;s Asset/Liability Models to project the core earnings stream (net interest income) of the company, and evaluating sensitivities to those earnings</li>
	<li>Supporting the capital and liquidity analysis, execution and maintenance of new structured finance transactions</li>
	<li>Working with senior business leaders on the design, development and execution of strategic Corporate Treasury change initiatives</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Impressive academic qualifications, and consistently strong performance in A&ndash;levels and university will need to be combined with drive, innovation and an understanding of global financial markets, products and tools. Sound quantitative skills, ideally supported by a good understanding of statistics, will be important. You should also have teamwork and problem&ndash;solving skills, and a willingness to accept responsibility and ask tough questions. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
The best opportunity to learn about working life at the company is to experience it first&ndash;hand through our nine&ndash;week Summer Programme. Aimed at students in their penultimate year, the programme runs from June to the end of August, and is designed to help you decide whether our offering matches your aspirations.  
</p>
<p class="bac">
The programme includes: 
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Classroom instruction prior to assignment </li>
	<li>Senior Speaker Series, featuring presentations by top executives </li>
	<li>Opportunities to interact with senior technologists and network with peers </li>
	<li>A mentoring programme</li>
	<li>Constructive feedback sessions through performance evaluations</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
If you perform well during your time, you may go back to university with a job offer for the following year, enabling you to truly focus on your studies. 
</p>

